page.title: 10ECOLOGY
page.content: RESIDENT BIRDS Nuthatch,Tree creeper and Wren breed commonly,as do Mistle Thrush,Song Thrush,Blackbird and Robin.Conifers support Goldcrests,gardens Hedge Sparrows and upland Meadow Pipits.Pied and Grey Wagtails nest near farms and streams.Starlings are ubiquitous,whereas finches present are Greenfinch,Bullfinch,Goldfinch,Chaffinc and Linnet as breeders,Siskins and Redpoll declining and Crossbills occasional.Buntings include Yellowhammer and Reed bunting.House Sparows abound. SUMMER MIGRANTS include the breeders Cuckoo,Swallow,House Martin,Winchat,Redstart,Blackcap,Garden Warbler,White throat,Lesser Whitethroat,Willow warbler,Chiffchaff,Wood Warbler,Spotted Flycatcher,Pied Flycatcher,Tree Pipit.
